This paper discusses algorithms for contextual multi-armed bandits, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on analyzing the performance of different algorithms in a stochastic and adversarial setting. The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and control systems (cs.SY).
